Sub-county small area estimates use state and county data from the CDC's Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System (BRFSS) in tandem with demographic data for census tracts and cities. It is not appropriate to use this data for evaluation purposes.
Census 2010 population counts and geographic boundaries data were used because corresponding Census 2020 population data are not available.
